    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="31"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d31">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72116/18½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have thought a great deal
                    about the matter of a protest with regard to the dropping of the bombs and my
                    present judgment is that we do not know in sufficient detail the actual facts
                    and that we ought to be very slow to make formal protests, chiefly because we
                    shall no doubt be called upon by every one of the belligerents before the
                    fighting is over to do something of this kind and would be in danger of becoming
                    chronic critics of what was going forward. I think the time for clearing up all
                    these matters will come when the war is over and the nations gather in sober
                    counsel again.</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
